               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors.&#xD;
Groups of lines on the incipit page of Text I and on the incipit page of the section for the night hours of Friday (in Text I-7); incipits of the texts, their sections and subsections; titles of the Biblical books and other works; directives for the ministers; names of Hebrew letters in Text I-7; the initial words of each paragraph of “Tǝmḫǝrtä ḫǝbuʾat” (in Text I-8); some other words, e.g., nastäbäqwǝʿ ḫabekä, Ǝgziʾo täśähalännä (and abbreviations), yǝbe mätärgwǝm, yǝtärägwǝm.&#xD;
Elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements; elements of the text dividers.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>On fol. 128vb, the “Homily of Jacob of Serug on Abraham” (in Text I-7) ends with a subscriptio ascribing the translation of the homily, from Arabic into Gǝʿǝz, to Metropolitan ʾabba Sälama (in tenure from 1350; cp. EAE IV, 488-89); besides, the original writing of the work is here attributed to Athanasius (Bishop of Alexandria from 328 to 373; cp. EAE I, 392):</note>
                     <note>ዝንቱ፡ ድርሳን፨ ዘአጽሐፎ፡ አቡነ፡ አባ፡ ሰላማ፡ ጳጳስ፡ ርቱዓ፡ ሃይማኖት፨ እምአረቢ፡ ለግዕዝ፤ ወይተሉ፡ ዝየ፡ ተጽሕፎ፡ ዘይቤ፡ ቅዱስ፡ አባ፡ አትናቴዮስ፨ ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ … አሜን።.</note>
                     <note>Cp. the note, e.g., in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESgbi002">GBI-002</ref>, fol. 99rc, in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESgms001">GMS-001</ref>, fol. 127rb, and in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqg004">AQG-004</ref>, fol. 104va.</note>
                  </msItem>
